-- Thailand Stocks: Nation Multimedia, Siam Commercial, Sahaviriya
-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 2012-04-27T09:44:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-27/thailand-stocks-nation-siam-commercial-samggi-sahaviriya.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Thailand  trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 4:30 p.m. close in Bangkok.  The  SET Index (SET)  rose 0.2 percent to 1,211.78, the highest
close since July 1996. The gauge gained 1.4 percent this week,
its second weekly advance.  Nation Multimedia Group Pcl (NMG)  , a newspaper publisher
and television broadcaster, jumped 18 percent to 1.05 baht, the
highest close since July 28. Shareholders yesterday approved a
proposal to reduce the company’s paid-up capital by 47 percent
to 873.3 million baht ($28.3 million) to compensate for
accumulated losses of 776.5 million baht, it said in a
regulatory filing.  Siam Commercial Samaggi Insurance Pcl (SCSMG)  , a non-
life insurer, surged 11 percent to 18.9 baht, the highest close
since Oct. 21. Net income in the first quarter climbed 30
percent to 107.1 million baht.  Sahaviriya Steel Industries Pcl (SSI)  , the nation’s
largest steel producer, dropped 2.6 percent to 0.76 baht, the
steepest decline since April 10. The company plans to sell 1.65
billion baht of convertible bonds, it said in a regulatory
filing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
